article:
About 8,000 'Fellows' have been elected to the Royal Society of London since its
inception in 1660. Below is an incomplete list of people who are or were
[[Fellow of the Royal Society|Fellows]] or Foreign Members of the Royal Society.
The date of election to the Fellowship follows the name. Dates in brackets
relate to an award or event associated with the person. The Society maintains
complete online lists of [http://www.royalsoc.ac.uk/page.asp?id=2210 current
Fellows] and of
[http://royalsociety.org/WorkArea/DownloadAsset.aspx?id=4294972811 past and
current Fellows]. This list is complete up to and including 2011.
